name: Partial response
body: This release is a small update to the gateway's handling of errors

This update includes the following features:
- Operation names are included in backing services
- Certain locations can be priortized over the others (useful for A/B testing)
- Fixed error code reporting 

Note: This update comes thanks to the awesome people over at Splunk! Special shout out to @bk-splunk @bardhi @jbreeden-splunk @edwinmo-splunk

name: Fixed handling of multiple operations
body:
This release is the first API-breaking change in the pre-release development of nautilus!

This fixes the way the gateway handles multiple operations through the `operationName` value in the http payload

name: Fixed memory leak
body: This release fixes a memory-leak that was uncovered by a few different users. Thanks again @bk-splunk!

name: Fixed errors when using nested objects as variables
v0.0.6
body: This release adds support for handling incoming batch requests as described [here](https://blog.apollographql.com/batching-client-graphql-queries-a685f5bcd41b).

name: v0.0.5
body: This release added gateway fields for further customizability. See README for details.

name: v0.0.4
body: This release fixed the resolution of the node field on the gateway.
This release includes a fix that removes the `id` field added as part of the execution process.
